title: Rimpfischhorn
text:
The Rimpfischhorn (4,199 m) is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in the <a href="Pennine%20Alps">Pennine</a> <a href="Swiss%20Alps">Alps</a> of <a href="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>.
The <a href="first%20ascent">first ascent</a> of the mountain was by <a href="Leslie%20Stephen">Leslie Stephen</a> and Robert Living with guides <a href="Melchior%20Anderegg">Melchior Anderegg</a> and Johann Zumtaugwald on 9 September 1859. Their route of ascent was from Fluh Alp via the Rimpfischwänge.
